name: tail

params.name: source
params.description: DataFrames will show the last *count* rows of that DataFrame. A list, tuple or other iterable, will show the last *count* rows. Dictionaries will show *count* keys from the dictionary, which will be randomly selected unless you are using an OrderedDict. Strings will show the last *count* characters.

params.name: count
params.description: The number of elements to show from the source.

doc: The opposite of the head function. Displays the last *count* elements of the *source* object.
